<HL>
   Bath Iron Works Gets Contract
</HL>
<DATE>
12/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   MD LIT GE
</CO>
<IN>
AEROSPACE (ARO)
</IN>
<GV>
DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)
</GV>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- Bath Iron Works Corp. was issued a $72.5
million Navy contract for destroyer shipyard services.
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   McDonnell Douglas Corp. got a $52.5 million in contracts
for Air Force aircraft testing and modification and for Army
helicopter improvements.
                                                                                                       

   Metro Machine Corp. received a $46.9 million Navy contract
for ship-maintenance services.
                                                                                                       

   Ingalls Shipbuilding Inc., a unit of Litton Industries
Inc., was awarded a $28.7 million Navy contract for destroyer
overhaul.
                                                                                                       

   Hercules Engines Inc. got a $13.5 million Army contract
for multifuel engines.
                                                                                                       

   General Electric Co. was awarded a $12.7 million Army
contract for transmissions.
</TEXT>
